Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes. Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant to have no contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.   Defendant to comply with GPS monitoring through Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant is not to come within 1 mile of Victim A, listed in the Victim Identification Key, or their residence, employment, school or anywhere they frequent.  The Defendant to report to WCS within 1 business day of being released. Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms.

8:36 AM Defendant Justyn N Wooten in court, in custody. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Niki Kane. Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. Court advises of right to an attorney. The defendant is currently being represented by Attorney Maura Mcmahon on his other felony matter. Court notes the probable cause section of both cases are exactly the same with the exception of the last few paragraphs to include an enhancer for a domestic abuse repeater. The State is willing to move to dismiss the 22CF331 matter and move forward with this case. The Court will dismiss the 22CF331 matter. The Court will set this matter back for status of counsel. Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.
Hearing scheduled for November 3, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Motion and Order to Seal Victim/Witness Identification Key signed by Judge Paul F Reilly October 13, 2022.
Victim/Witness Identification Key filed, under seal, by the District Attorney's office.
